Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
define_parameter(25.10)                                define_parameter(25.10)

Name
       define_parameter - Provides variation information to Tempus

Syntax
       define_parameter

        [-help]

       [<setup | hold>]

        [-correlation <string>]

       [-distribution <string>]

        [-moments <string>]

        [-name <string>]

        [-range <string>]

       [-related <string>]

        -scope <string>

        [-view <string>]

       Provides  variation information to Tempus. You can directly specify the
       range information and Tempus will internally calculate moments and  use
       it for wire variation calculation.

Parameters
       -help  Prints out the command usage.

       setup | hold
              Defines parameter that is valid for setup or hold.

       -correlation <<string>>
              Specifies  correlation  between different parameters of the same
              scope - parameters need to be pre-defined.

       -distribution <<string>>
              Specifies the parameter distribution. You can also use  user-de-
              fined distribution.

       -moments <<string>>
              Specifies the parameter moments - mean or std-dev.

       -name <<string>>
              Specifies the name of the parameter.

       -range <<string>>
              Specifies the parameter minimum or maximum range - min or max.

       -related <<sting>>
              Specifies  the  related  information  on  sub-scope of parameter
              within the specified -scope.

              For back end-of-line (BEOL), the allowed arguments are:

              * <layer  name>: capacitance

              * <layer name>:resistance

       -scope <<string>>
              Specifies the  parameter  scope  -  vtskew,  wire_variation,  or
              via_variation.

       -view <<string>>
              Specifies the view name.

Examples
              * The  following  command defines R/C range for normal distribu-
                tion for M1 layer for setup for view view1:

                define_parameter setup -view  view1  -name  param_M1_R  -scope
                wire_variation -distribution gaussian -range {1 1.15}

                define_parameter  setup  -view  view1 -name -param_M1_C -scope
                wire_variation -distribution gaussian -range {0.95 1}

              * The following command defines R/C moments for normal distribu-
                tion for M1 layer for setup for all views:

                define_parameter setup -name param_M1_R -scope  wire_variation
                -distribution gaussian -moments {0.2 0.01}

                define_parameter  setup -name param_M1_C -scope wire_variation
                -distribution gaussian -moments {0.95 1}

              * The following command defines correlation between metal layers
                - if M1, M2 and M3 are fully correlating:

                define_parameter    -scope    wire_variation      -correlation
                {{param_M1_C param_M2_C param_M3_C} {1.0}}

Related Information
